## 4. Detailed Findings

Organize by: 4.1 Current State, 4.2 Regulatory Landscape, 4.3 Technology & Data, 4.4 Market Dynamics, 4.5 Future State, 4.6 Risk & Controls, 4.7 Timeline (if applicable).

### Finding Format

> **F[#]: [Title]** `[Q-ref]`
> 
> **Finding**: [Evidenced fact]
> 
> **Sources**: [Full URL(s) with dates]
> 
> **Confidence**: [High/Medium/Low] ‚Äî [Justification]
> 
> **So What?**: [Why it matters‚Äîevidence-based interpretation. Use `[INFERENCE]` only for speculative implications.]

### Confidence Levels

| Level | Definition | Standard |
|-------|------------|----------|
| **High** | Well-established | 2+ Tier 1‚Äì2 sources OR 1 unambiguous Tier 1 |
| **Medium** | Likely accurate, some uncertainty | 1 Tier 1‚Äì2 OR multiple Tier 3 in agreement |
| **Low** | Plausible, significant uncertainty | Tier 3‚Äì4 only, limited corroboration |
| **Speculative** | Cannot assess | Noted in Appendix C; no confident claim |

### Inference Rule
Label speculative implications with `[INFERENCE]`. Keep minimal and clearly justified.

